PyRogue v0.2.0 Summer 2026 By Andrew Butler
Built with Python 3.14

This is the core PyRogue game 'engine', if you want to call it something so fancy.

This package handles all the game logic, allows calls to influence the game, and is capable of giving the 
current game state. It requires a frontend/UI implementation, as it does not include one on its own.

This is the third itteration of this project; the first was a C/C++ series of assignments for one of my
university classes, and the second was the same Python game logic seen here but with a hardcoded Tkinter-based
UI. Both of these are still accessible on the 'Legacy_C++' and 'tkinter-ui' branches, respectively.
Neither the C++ code nor the tkinter UI version will be receiving updates.

Notes for myself:
- selection and control options should be based on what they do; probably need to specify and convert to enums
- Rendering methods need deleted and decoupled from existing code; will need to test that nothing breaks, although I think 
    I will need a UI to do that. I guess that also means I should make the UI it's own thing as well.


